<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>FishNiNi – A Mythic World for the Free</title>
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <style>
      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: 'Georgia', serif;
        color: #333;
        background-color: #fffaf0;
      }
      header {
        background: <i center/cover no-repeat;
        height: 100vh;
        color: white;
        text-shadow: 0 0 6px #000;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
        flex-direction: column;
        padding: 2rem;
      }
      header h1 {
        font-size: 4rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      header p {
        font-size: 1.4rem;
        max-width: 700px;
        text-align: center;
      }
      section {
        padding: 4rem 2rem;
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: auto;
      }
      h2 {
        font-family: 'Palatino Linotype', serif;
        font-size: 2rem;
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      }
      .grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
        gap: 2rem;
      }
      .card {
        background: #fff;
        border: 1px solid #eee;
        border-radius: 12px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
        box-shadow: 0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
      }
      footer {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 2rem;
        background: #111;
        color: #eee;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>

    <header>
      <h1>Welcome to FishNiNi</h1>
      <p>A mythic world not for children, but for the wanderers of soul and spirit. This is not a storybook – it's a mirror of who you could become.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>About the World</h2>
      <p>
        In this realm, kings are not born but chosen. Magic doesn't solve problems – it reveals who you are. 
        Here, fairies debate politics, dragons practice meditation, and lost travelers find not treasure, but questions.
        <br /><br />
        <strong>Unishell</strong> is a fairytale for grown souls: complex, quiet, haunted, and hopeful.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Realms You May Wander</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Forest of Unlearning</h3>
          <p>Where memories dissolve like mist and you're forced to find a new self without your past.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>The Hollow Court</h3>
          <p>A palace of echoing laughter and shadow games. Nothing is real, except what you truly want.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h3>Mirrored Lake</h3>
          <p>Each ripple shows another version of you. Some you admire. Some you fear.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Whispers from the World</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <p>“You cannot survive as they do. You are made of storms.”</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <p>“Not all monsters hide under beds. Some wear your smile.”</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <p>“Freedom isn't escape. It's choosing to stay where truth hurts.”</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer>
      <p>© 2025 Unishell. Walk gently, dream fiercely.</p>
    </footer>

  </body>
</html>
